[3
Date: Thu, 14 Jan 1999 14:22:31 +1000
From: <p.prociv@mailbox.uq.oz.au>

It might be just a crazy long shot, but were these greyhounds tested
for the effects of anticoagulant rodenticides (they were Greyhounds,
after all. . . . )? Did clinical pathology findings from the
affected dogs before they died include PT/APTT, bleeding time or
platelet numbers? There was no mention of it in the ProMED-mail
post.
--
